- We are not doing any changes for rabbitmq
- so that we can run the rabbitmq directly using the docker image provided by rabbitmq
- we can run the rabbitmq server using the following command
- `docker run -d \
     --name rabbitmq \
     --network roboshop \
     -e RABBITMQ_DEFAULT_USER=roboshop \
     -e RABBITMQ_DEFAULT_PASS=roboshop123 \
     rabbitmq:3`
- this will start the rabbitmq server on port 4369